    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I am glad the prints are arrived &amp; hope they will be as much liked with you
                    as in <placeName ref="pl0775">England</placeName>. is the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora Scotica</title></bibl> come? Thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> intelligence about my poor friend.<note type="editorial">Possibly a reference to the death of <persName ref="pe0022">Robert Ramsay</persName> at the end of the previous year.</note> if you
                    can send me a catalogue of his curiosities I shall be glad. I fear you forget
                    the descent of <persName ref="pe0090">Lord Fife</persName> The occupation of his
                    grandsire &amp; the means they got at wealth. I shall observe strict
                    silence.</p>
                <p>I find by the return of my <persName ref="pe0111">Bookseller</persName> that my
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">Welsh Tour</title></bibl> has
                    done very well. So I shall on with spirit with another part &amp; hope to
                    produce it at Christmas. I shall soon send you another proof for <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lows</persName> benefit which I
                    trust will please. I love to promote merit. I fear he forgets his promise of a
                    skua to my friend <persName ref="pe0033">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                        Blackburn</persName>. inclosed is a cancel for you for my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">Welsh Tour</title></bibl>.</p>
                <closer><salute>With <lb/>great truth I rest y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <lb/><signed><persName ref="pe0232">Th. Pennant.</persName></signed>
                    <dateline>March 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1779.</dateline></closer>

            </div>
        </body>
